	The responsibilities of the Emergency Response Person at the facility are:

1)	identify the source of the release and/or spill;  
2)	make sure that employees who are not trained to handle the specific release and/or spill are evacuated from the area;
3)	evaluate the extent of the release and/or spill, i.e. whether employees are injured requiring medical attention and if it would be considered an on-site or an off-site release;
4)	in the event of an off-site release or exposure to personnel, immediately notify the local fire department for assistance;
5)	Notify the Corporate Environmental Director within five (5) minutes for further notification to the appropriate local, state and/or national agencies within fifteen (15) minutes;

(g)	Planned changes to improve safety.

Existing programs and continued training of employees will ensure that adequate safety precautions are in place at the facility.
